GxClientModels

Interface GxClientFilterModel

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GxClientFilterAbstractModel, GxClientFilterBooleanModel, GxClientFilterCombinedModel, GxClientFilterDateTimeModel, GxClientFilterNumberModel, GxClientFilterSetFilterModel, GxClientFilterSimpleModel, GxClientFilterTextModel

    public interface GxClientFilterModel
    When saving or restoring state on a filter the filter model is used. The filter model represents the state of the filter
    Author:
    Hyyan Abo Fakher

      • apply

        BBjString apply(BBjNumber send!)
        Apply the filter This method will only compose the model and send it to the client in case `send!` is true. On the client the new model will be displayed on the filter panel but it will not be applied on the data. To execute the model on the client you need to call `execute(1)`
        Parameters:
        BBjNumber - send! when true the model will be send to the client , false otherwise
        Returns:
        BBjString The generated js code used to apply the model
        Throws:
        256 - when the column or the widget are not defined
        See Also:
        GxClientFilterModel.execute()

      • apply

      • execute

        BBjString execute(BBjNumber send!)
        Tell the grid to refresh rows based on the filter. the filter does not do this automatically in case multiple filters are going to get set.
        Parameters:
        BBjNumber - send! when true the execution code will executed on the client , false otherwise
        Returns:
        BBjString The generated js code used to execute the model on the client
        Throws:
        256 - when the column or the widget are not defined
